# factoredInteger

- _factoredInteger([p₁ e₁; p₂ e₂ …])_

Answer the factored object corresponding to a factorization.

```
>>> 12.factorInteger
[2 2; 3 1]

>>> [2 2; 3 1].factoredInteger
12
```

* * *

See also: factorInteger, isPrimeFactorization

Guides: Integer Functions, Prime Number Functions

